abstract.p: Panel discussion on New York City Buildings Department, scheduled for May 18, is canceled (S)

block.p: A panel discussion on the New York City Buildings Department scheduled for tomorrow evening, described in an article in the Real Estate section on Sunday, has been canceled. All five of the department's borough superintendents were to have taken part in the discussion, sponsored by the New York Chapter of the American Institute of Architects. The organizer, Steven Zirinsky, and a spokeswoman for the agency, Ilyse Fink, said scheduling conflicts had caused the cancellation.
